718567f-a.text:
(1) Centre Street, west side, north from Worth Street. This view
shows the tombs.
February 24, 1929.

NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, from a different angle, showing a further view north
on Centre Street. Also shown is Leohard Street, west from Centre,
to and including Lafayette Streets. Included also is Lafayette
Street, west side, north from but not including Leonard, to but not
including Franklin Streets. In the foreground is shown a clear-
ance for the Department of Health Building.
March 27, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

719735f-a.title: Manhattan: Centre Street - Worth Street
719735f-a.text:
Foley Square The New York State Bldg. as viewed eastward from
lafayette at Worth Streets. This structure,No. 80 Centre Street,
is also bounded, by Worth, Leonard and Baxter Streets and was the first
building erected here of this civic center. The latest is the Board
of Health structure and is seen on the left. To the right appears a
portion of the New York County Court House.
June 12, 1938.
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

719739f-a.title: Manhattan: Foley Square - Centre Street
719739f-a.text:
Foley Square (unofficially called Court House Scuare,) north from
Duane Street, at the intersection of Centre, Lafayette, Pearl and Duane
Streets. Buildings as seen from left to right are the Tombs, New York
State Building, The New York County Court House and the old building of the
Department of Health.
About 1930.
Ewing Galloway.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
